.TH "vmw_validation_res_set_dirty" 9 "vmw_validation_res_set_dirty" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_validation_res_set_dirty \- Register a resource dirty set or clear during validation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" vmw_validation_res_set_dirty
.BI "(struct vmw_validation_context *ctx "  ","
.BI "void *val_private "  ","
.BI "u32 dirty "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
The validation context.
.IP "val_private" 12
The additional meta-data pointer returned when the
resource was registered with the validation context. Used to identify
the resource.
.IP "dirty" 12
Dirty information VMW_RES_DIRTY_XX
